Police have confirmed the discovery of a body on a beach in north Cornwall.A man was reported missing in the Northcott Mouth area of Bude on 4 June.The swimmer's disappearance prompted a search by HM Coastguard, the RNLI, police and paramedics but it was called off the following day.Devon and Cornwall Police, which was called to the Crackington Haven area at 20:45 BST on Tuesday, said formal identification had yet to take place but the man's family had been made aware.
